edu.ncsu.csc216.book_quiz.question
Class QuestionState

java.lang.Object
  edu.ncsu.csc216.book_quiz.question.QuestionState
Direct Known Subclasses:
BookQuestions.AdvancedQuestionState, BookQuestions.ElementaryQuestionState, BookQuestions.StandardQuestionState
public abstract class QuestionState
extends java.lang.Object

An abstract class that represents state in the FSM. QuestionState is extended by private inner classes nested inside BookQuestions.

Author:
AlexiaMoore

Method Detail

processAnswer

public abstract java.lang.String processAnswer(java.lang.String answer)
                                        throws EmptyQuestionListException
Abstract method to process the user's answer. Throws an EmptyQuestionListException if currentQuestion is null. This method corresponds to transitions in the FSM. Each concrete state (nested classes inside BookQuestions) defines this method according to the transitions that go from that state.

Parameters:
answer - the answer to be processed
Returns:
the String that is appropriate for a response to the given answer
Throws:
EmptyQuestionListException - if there are no more questions to process in the state

hasMoreQuestions

public boolean hasMoreQuestions()

Returns:
true if there are more questions, false otherwise

nextQuestion

public void nextQuestion()
Sets currentQuestion to the next item in the waitingQuestions list, or null if there are no more questions in the list. The currentQuestion is added to the end of the askedQuestions list.

addQuestion

public void addQuestion(edu.ncsu.csc216.question_library.Question question)
Adds the given question to the end of the waitingQuestions list. If currentQuestion is null, implying there are no more questions of that type to ask, nextQuestion() is executed because there is now a question to ask.

Parameters:
question - the question to add to the end of the waitingQuestions list

getQuestions

public java.util.List<edu.ncsu.csc216.question_library.Question> getQuestions()
Returns a list of questions. The list of questions combines the askedQuestions with the waitingQuestions. The askedQuestions are added to the joint list first.

Returns:
questions the list of all the questions
